        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 6 at 2:34AM CDT until May 6 at 3:30AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 234 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 9 miles south of
Christoval, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Two inch hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

This severe storm will be near...
Christoval around 240 AM CDT.
Vancourt around 305 AM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this severe thunderstorm include The
Intersection Of Ranch Road 1828 And Ranch Road 915.
</description>
        <instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 400 AM CDT for west central
Texas.

For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
